Predictive Analysis of
'Most Valuable Player’
About 'Most Valuable Player' award
Annual award given by MLB (Major League Baseball)
Given to outstanding Baseball player
Players who are good at Batting, Pitching and Fielding are eligible.
Players who are not actively playing or retired are not eligible
Source of Data
"Baseball Databank" from Kaggle
https://www.kaggle.com/open-source-sports/baseball-databank)
Master.csv - Player details
Batting.csv - Batting statistics
Pitching.csv – Pitching statistics
Fielding.csv - Fielding statistics
AwardsPlayers.csv - Awards won by baseball players
Appearances.csv - Positions at which a player appeared.
Technologies Used
Pandas
Numpy
Plotly
Scikit-learn
Machine Learning Models:
 Logistic Regression
 Random Forest Classifier
Data Cleanup & Preparation
Eliminate the players those are not actively playing
Eliminate the players those are already retired
Eliminate the players those are not alive
Aggregate the data of players palyed in different roles, Following are few of them:
 Number of games played overall
 Number of games played in Batting role
 Number of games played in Pitching role
 Number of homeruns made overall
 Number of years played overall
Select only the actively playing players for further analysis
Train & Test Data for Machine Learning Model:
Split the dataset into players who won 'Most Valuable Player' award
and who never own.
"Train data" is the data of players who wont the 'Most Valuable
Player' award in the past.
"Test data" is the data of players who never won 'Most Valuable
Player'
Predictive Machine Learning Model
Applied both 'Logistic Regression' and 'Random Forest Classifier’
Observed optimal accuracy with 'Random Forest Classifier'
Fit 'Random Forest Classifier' to get the predictions
Find top 10 players those have more chances of winning 'Most
Valuable Player' award
